The Platform API provides developers with a RESTful interface for the configuration of BackChat.io user's accounts, Channels, and Streams.
<h2>Endpoints</h2>
Please see the <a title="Platform API endpoints" href="http://support.backchat.io/platform-api-endpoints/">Platform API endpoint documentation</a> entry for information on available endpoints.
<h2>Response format</h2>
All responses are of type application/javascript.
<pre class="brush:js">{
  "data": {
    /* Response data JSON goes here */
  }
  "errors": [
    /* Response errors go here, in an array format:
     * ["", "global error message"]
     * ["fieldname", "error message"]
     */
  ]
}</pre>
<h2>HTTPS</h2>
All endpoints are available over <strong>HTTPS only</strong>.
<h2>Rate limiting</h2>
Currently we do not implement rate limiting.
<h2>Pagination</h2>
Currently we do not implement pagination.
